    "millsfield:images_texts": [
      "FROM AMFRICAN AIRLINES\nNewest type commercial air transport to enter scheduled airline\nservice is American Arlines DC-6B Flegehip shown here in 111ght.\nAnerican Inaugurated transcontinental service with the new plane on\nApr11 29th of this year between New York and Ios Angeles. A larger\nversion of the famed DC-6 Flagship, the DC-6B 1s five feet longer and\nprovides additional space for cargo in forward cargo compartments.\nThe\nnew plane acconnodates 52 passengers with six additional seats located\nin the observation lounge; it has a cruleing speed of 300 miles per hour\nand a range of 2,900 miles at 20,000 feet. Four Pratt and Whitney Double\nWarp 18 cylinder engines can develop a total of 9,600 horsepower; 1te\nmaximum take-off weight 1s 100,000 pounds; landings 85,000 pounds.\nAmerican has ordered 17 of the new craft from the Douglas Aircraft Co.\nfor delivery during 1951.\n-AAs\nREF52351\nPhoto #15806-B\nMICHAEL\nKLAAS\n2018.112.0042",
      "N90755\nAMERICAN\nAMERICAN AIRL\nNES®"
